text: A military parade at the height of a modern army that has impressed the heights of Algeria by a great mastery and an outstanding discipline.
In a speech, the President of the Republic, Abdel-Majid Abouna, said that the commemoration of this memorable anniversary,
embodying glory, dignity and pride, is the opportunity to remind that Algeria, which triumphed from colonialism yesterday,
continues to achieve victories with all confidence thanks to its children.
The parade began with the overflight of an air formation composed of L-39 aircraft,
air forces that decorated the sky of the capital with national colors.
100 air demonstrations were followed by advanced training aircraft,
Yak-130s and air force executions.
In a demonstration of refueling in flight of two Su-24 aircraft by a refueling aircraft,
escorted by four MiG-29 aircraft and the training parade of several helicopters,
including those specialized in reconnaissance and provisioning and training of three drones,
also participated in this military parade, the square of the different formations.
Fighting vehicle formations also took to the lead tanks of different types.
The President of the Republic and his hosts have long applauded the impressive performance
and the remarkable development of the Army of Independent Algeria,
an army loyal to the November Sermon.
The parade allowed to immortalize the epic of November 1954
and to galvanize the energies for a victorious Algeria,
as dreamed by the Shuhada and the Mujahideen of the glorious Revolution of Liberation.
A large crowd attended the parade, which was marked by a rigorous organization.
